article.description: Cal St. Fullerton 76, Cal St. Northridge 72
article.headline: Cal St. Fullerton 76, Cal St. Northridge 72
article.linkText: Cal St. Fullerton 76, Cal St. Northridge 72
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. (AP) -- Bobby Brown scored 15 of his 23 points in the second half as Cal State Fullerton rallied for a 76-72 victory over Cal State Northridge on Thursday. Frank Robinson added season highs of 17 points and eight rebounds for the Titans (11-3, 2-1 Big West), who have won six of their past seven games and 11 straight at home over two seasons. Jason Hill scored a career-best 21 points for the Matadors (6-7, 0-2), who have lost six of eight and remain winless on the road. Rob Haynes added a career-high 18 points and Thomas Shewmake grabbed nine rebounds. Northridge began the second half with a 16-2 surge that turned a 39-26 halftime deficit into a 42-41 lead with 12:48 to play. But Fullerton used a 10-2 spurt to move ahead 54-46 with 8:47 left before building an 11-point lead with 6:29 to go. Haynes' 3-point shot narrowed the deficit to 69-66 with 2:07 to play. But Fullerton's Justin Burns stole the ball, got fouled while scoring a layup and made the ensuing free throw to extend the Titans' lead to 72-66 with 1:04 left. Fullerton set a single-game school record for most 3-point shots attempted, 33.
